  "caption": "Figure 4 Quadriviridae. Phylogenetic tree of the RdRP of quadriviruses, chrysoviruses and some members of the family Totiviridae . Translated sequences were aligned using MUSCLE ( Edgar 2004 ) as implemented in SSE v1.3 ( Simmonds 2012 ), and the least divergent region (amino acid positions 679 to 1066, numbered according to the RdRP of Rosellinia necatrix quadrivirus 1 strain W1075) was used to produce a midpoint rooted maximum likelihood dendrogram in MEGA7 ( Kumar et al., 2016 ) using the LG model with a gamma distribution of substitution rates and a proportion of invariant sites. Numbers at the nodes denote bootstrap values where these were > 70%. The scale bar represents the amino acid distances. This phylogenetic tree and corresponding sequence alignment are available to download from the Resources page .",
